com.soa.message

Class SimpleMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.soa.message.AbstractMessage
      • com.soa.message.SimpleMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Message

    public class SimpleMessage
extends AbstractMessage
    Simple implementation of the Message interface. No protocol specific implementation provided. The message reports its normalized as the normalization functions do not do anything.

      • normalizeToXML

        public Message normalizeToXML()
                       throws com.digev.fw.exception.GException
        Description copied from interface: Message
        Normalizes the message to an XML format. All defined message parts are taken from their bound encodings and placed in the message's parts map. The part identified as the content part (see Message.getContentPartName()) will be translated into an XML representation. A new normalized version of the message is returned. Due to the possibility of this original object using InputStreams to hold its content, after normalization this object's InputStreams will most likely be exhausted making this object unusable. To continue to use this object after normalization in its original bound format, use Message.normalizeCopyToXML() instead.
        Returns:
        Normalized Message.
        Throws:
        com.digev.fw.exception.GException - Thrown if unable to normalize.

      • normalizeCopyToXML

        public Message normalizeCopyToXML()
                           throws com.digev.fw.exception.GException
        Description copied from interface: Message
        Normalizes the message to an XML format leaving the original bound object unchanged. All defined message parts are taken from their bound encodings and placed in the message's parts map. The part identified as the content part (see Message.getContentPartName()) will be translated into an XML representation. A new normalized version of the message is returned. In order to leave the original object in tact it must be copied which may be expensive from a performance perspective.
        Returns:
        Normalized Message.
        Throws:
        com.digev.fw.exception.GException - Thrown if unable to normalize.

Due to the possibility of this original object using InputStreams to hold its content, after normalization this object's InputStreams will most likely be exhausted making this object unusable.       • normalizeCopy

        public Message normalizeCopy()
                      throws com.digev.fw.exception.GException
        Description copied from interface: Message
        Normalizes the message leaving the original bound object unchanged. All defined message parts are taken from their bound encodings and placed in the message's parts map. A new normalized version of the message is returned. In order to leave the original object intact it must be copied which may be expensive from a performance perspective.

      • copy

        public Message copy()
             throws com.digev.fw.exception.GException
        Description copied from interface: Message
        Create a copy of the message. Message normalization state and content are left intact. The returned message will have a copy of the message internal state, including any message properties.
        Returns:
        A copy of this Message.
        Throws:
        com.digev.fw.exception.GException - Thrown if unable to copy.
